name: TDL-Exploit-Driver
description: A driverless driver that is supposed to be manually mapped, usually by using TDL exploit. The driver shows how to read/write to any process memory and some other useful functions.

name: DBC2
description: DBC2 (DropboxC2) is a modular post-exploitation tool, composed of an agent running on the victim's machine, a controler, running on any machine, powershell modules, and Dropbox servers as a means of communication.
